{
  "texts": [
    "The proposed approach performs two tasks during two main phases.",
    "First, the segmentation architecture was trained on BUS images and their corresponding masks to extract the tumor region from its surroundings in the image.",
    "Secondly, the proposed approach enhances its performance by exploiting the potential of transformers, in which an adapted ViT model was employed for the classification of the segmented tumor region.",
    "Additionally, we investigated the MLP-Mixer to capitalize on its ability to classify BUS images by relying solely on MLP blocks without the need for high computational resources for training and inference.",
    "Figure 1 shows an overview of the proposed framework."
  ]
}